Allows the app to continue a call which was started in another app.

This app can get your location based on network sources such as cell towers and Wi-Fi networks. These location services must be turned on and available on your phone for the app to be able to use them.
Allows an application to provision and use DRM certficates. Should never be needed for normal apps.

This app can get your location based on GPS or network location sources such as cell towers and Wi-Fi networks. These location services must be turned on and available on your phone for the app to be able to use them. This may increase battery consumption.
Allows the app to use the IMS service to make calls without your intervention.
Allows the app to access extra location provider commands. This may allow the app to interfere with the operation of the GPS or other location sources.

Allows the app to view information about network connections such as which networks exist and are connected.

Allows the app to view information about Wi-Fi networking, such as whether Wi-Fi is enabled and name of connected Wi-Fi devices.

Allows the app to read and write Do Not Disturb configuration.
Allows the app to add messages to your voicemail inbox.
Allows the app to answer an incoming phone call.

Allows the app to configure the local Bluetooth phone, and to discover and pair with remote devices.
Allows the app to access data from sensors that monitor your physical condition, such as your heart rate.
Allows the app to send sticky broadcasts, which remain after the broadcast ends. Excessive use may make the phone slow or unstable by causing it to use too much memory.

Allows the app to change the state of network connectivity.
Allows the app to change the state of tethered network connectivity.

Allows the app to connect to and disconnect from Wi-Fi access points and to make changes to device configuration for Wi-Fi networks.
Allows the app to connect the phone to and disconnect the phone from WiMAX networks.
Allows the app to manage telecom connections.
Allows the app to provide an in-call user experience.

Allows the app to create network sockets and use custom network protocols. The browser and other applications provide means to send data to the internet, so this permission is not required to send data to the internet.

Allows the app to manage network policies and define app-specific rules.
Allows the app to route its calls through the system in order to improve the calling experience.

This permission allows apps to save your contact data, and malicious apps may share contact data without your knowledge."
